text: Kay Schrøder (1 July 1877 - 25 April 1949) was a Danish fencer and architect. He competed in three fencing events at the 1920 Summer Olympics. He also competed in the architecture event in the art competition at the 1924 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1877 births Category:1949 deaths Category:Danish male fencers Category:Olympic fencers of Denmark Category:Fencers at the 1920 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Copenhagen Category:19th-century Danish architects Category:20th-century Danish architects Category:Olympic competitors in art competitions
